=============
Up in the sky
=============

.. class:: right

*RIPE NCC TS Lab Environment*

.. class:: right

*Andrzej Wolski*

.. raw:: pdf

    PageBreak regularPage

.. contents:: `Agenda`
    :depth: 1
    :class: thin

Goal
----------------

- get hands on experience

Requirements
------------

- modular building blocks
- open source components
- replicable
- web based
- easy to pick up
- no additional load for Trainers

Phases
------

- virtual with AWS
- virtual with a second cloud provider
- local
- physical

Building blocks ( infrastructure )
----------------------------------

- EC2 ( *compute* )
- S3 ( *storage* )
- VPC ( *network* )

.. image:: images/aws.png
    :align: right
    :width: 1000

Building blocks ( software )
----------------------------

- python ( *high level programming language* )
- boto ( *AWS API python library* )
- django ( *Python web framework* )
- coffescript ( *JavaScript wrapper* )
- html5 boilerplate ( *for unified experience between browsers* )
- puppet ( *server bootstrap and configuration* )
- shell in a box ( *local shell access* )

Architecture ( infrastructure )
-------------------------------

- replicable always on "instructor"
- routers based on Vyatta ( Cisco like CLI )
- hosts based on Linux ( well known tooling )
- IPv6 tunnelling

Architecture ( overview )
-------------------------

.. image:: images/labs_overview.png
    :align: center
    :width: 1600

Experience ( trainer )
----------------------

- web based "admin portal"
- labs auto deployable through "admin portal"
- monitoring of time and progress
- possibility to hijack user session

Experience ( attendee )
-----------------------

- single portal ( per attendee )
- all materials included on portal ( instructions and hints )
- possibility to interact with trainer ( call for help functionality )

Problems... sure
----------------

- AWS API instability
- AWS outages
- AWS no official IPv6 support
- multicast unexplained

Future
------

- multiple labs scenarios
- other cloud providers
- local deployment
- physical hardware hookups
- attendee registration
- feedback
- course reporting
- webinars
- build in group chat

Ready For Comments
------------------

**It's just an idea, help me to make it usable for everyone.**

